==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electrum
<hw>E*lec"trum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/.
See <er>Electric</er>, and cf. <er>Electre</er>,
<er>Electron</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Amber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An alloy of gold and silver, of an amber color, used
by the ancients.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>German-silver plate. See <cref>German silver</cref>,
under <er>German</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electuary</ent>⟦br⟧
